# Add new Panel Icons

When the user asks to add new icon(s) to the panel-icons library, follow this workflow.

## 1. Get the SVG and name

- Ask the user for each new icon:
  - The **SVG content** (full markup).
  - The **icon name** in kebab-case (e.g. `my-new-icon`).
- If multiple icons are added in one go, collect all names and SVGs before writing files.

## 2. Ensure fill is currentColor

- Before writing any SVG file, ensure fill uses `currentColor` so icons inherit text color.
- Set `fill="currentColor"` on the root `<svg>` element, or on any `<path>` / shape that should be colored. Replace hardcoded fills (e.g. `#000`, `black`) with `currentColor` where appropriate.
- Write the corrected SVG to disk.

## 3. Place files and build

- Before saving, **remove XML tags** from the SVG (e.g. `<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>`). Leaving them in can cause warnings later in the pipeline.
- Save each SVG as **`raw/<name>.svg`** (e.g. `raw/my-new-icon.svg`).
- Run **`npm run build`** so SVGO produces the optimized icons in **`icons/`**. Do not manually copy into `icons/`; the build step does that.
- If build fails, fix any SVG or config issues before continuing.

## 4. User creates the change file

- **Do not run `npm run change` yourself.** Instruct the user to run **`npm run change`** (and if it fails, to run **`npm install`** first, then try again).
- Wait for the user to confirm that the change file has been created in the **`change/`** folder (or check for a new file in `change/` when continuing).
- **Using the change file** to drive README updates:
  - Open the change file in `change/` (e.g. `change/@scayle-panel-icons-*.json`). It contains:
    - **`type`**: `"major"`, `"minor"`, or `"patch"` ‚Äî this determines the version bump.
    - **`comment`**: often mentions the new icon name(s); use this and the icons you added to build the ‚ÄúNew icons‚Äù list.
  - Read the current **`version`** from **`package.json`** (e.g. `4.3.0`). Compute the **new version** to bump to:
    - **patch**: increment patch (e.g. `4.3.0` ‚Üí `4.3.1`).
    - **minor**: increment minor, reset patch (e.g. `4.3.0` ‚Üí `4.4.0`).
    - **major**: increment major, reset minor and patch (e.g. `4.3.0` ‚Üí `5.0.0`).
  - Use this **new version** (the one we‚Äôre updating to) for all README upgrade guide updates in section 5.

## 5. Update the README

After the change file exists, update **README.md** to match existing patterns:

### 5.1 Icons count badge

- In the badges section (near the top), update the icons count badge so the number matches the total number of icons in `icons/`.
- Pattern: `https://img.shields.io/badge/icons-<COUNT>-success` (e.g. `icons-249-success` if there are 249 icons).

### 5.2 Icons table

- In the **## Icons** section, add one row per new icon.
- Keep the same structure as existing rows:
  - **Name**: kebab-case name, padded with spaces so the column aligns (same width as other names in the table).
  - **Icon**: `![](./icons/<name>.svg)` with consistent padding.
  - **Filename**: `` `./icons/<name>.svg` `` with consistent padding.
  - **Vue**: `` `<IconPascalCase class="icon" />` `` where PascalCase is the icon name with each hyphen-segment capitalized (e.g. `my-new-icon` ‚Üí `IconMyNewIcon`).
- Insert new rows in **alphabetical order** by icon name so the table stays sorted.
- Preserve the existing header and separator rows and the rest of the table formatting.

### 5.3 Upgrade guide

- The **‚Äú## Upgrade guide from version 3.0.0 to Y.Y.Y‚Äù** section at the top must refer to the version **we are updating to**: **Y.Y.Y** is the **new version** you computed from the change file (section 4).
- Update the next line to: **To upgrade your panel-icons library, change the version for @scayle/panel-icons to "^&lt;new&gt;"** (e.g. `"^4.4.0"`).
- Add or update the subsection: **#### New icons in version &lt;new&gt;** (e.g. `#### New icons in version 4.4.0`).
- Under it, add a bullet list of the new icon names in kebab-case, one per line (e.g. `- block`). Use the change file‚Äôs `comment` and the icons you added to build this list.

## Summary

1. Ask for SVG content and kebab-case name(s).
2. Set fill to `currentColor` in the SVG; remove XML tags (e.g. `<?xml ...?>`); write to `raw/<name>.svg`.
3. Run `npm run build` to update `icons/`.
4. **User** runs `npm run change` (remind them to run `npm install` if it fails). You use the new file in `change/` to get `type` and compute the new version (patch/minor/major bump from `package.json`).
5. Update README: badge count; Icons table (new rows, alphabetical); Upgrade guide ‚Äî set the **top** ‚Äú## Upgrade guide from version &lt;previous&gt; to &lt;new&gt;‚Äù to the version we‚Äôre updating to, and add ‚Äú#### New icons in version &lt;new&gt;‚Äù with the new icon list.
